title: Internet Users per 100 Population by country, 2014
description:
Internet Users per 100 People by country, repeated for each of the following years: 2000, 2005, 2010 to enable time-series display using the YEAR attribute. 
Internet users are individuals who have used the Internet (from any location) in the last 12 months. Internet can be used via a computer, mobile phone, personal digital assistant, games machine, digital TV etc. 
Data Sources: International Telecommunication Union, World Telecommunication/ICT Development Report and database, and World Bank estimates via World Bank DataBank; Natural Earth 50M scale data.
snippet: Internet Users per 100 Population by Country, 2014. This is a filtered layer based on the "Internet Users per 100 Population by country, 2000-2010 time series" layer.
accessInformation: International Telecommunication Union, World Telecommunication/ICT Development Report and database, and World Bank estimates via World Bank DataBank, Natural Earth, Maps.com
